# Part 1: Personal Computer Security {.center background-image="/assets/background1.png" background-size="cover"}

---

## Password Management {.center background-image="/assets/slide1.png" background-size="cover"}

> "Strong authentication is your first line of defense"

---

## Use a Password Manager {background-image="/assets/background1.png" background-size="cover"}

::: incremental
- Generate unique, complex passwords
- Store credentials securely
- Sync across devices safely
- Never remember passwords again
:::

---

## Enable Multi-Factor Authentication {background-image="/assets/slide1.png" background-size="cover"}

::: incremental
- **Email accounts** - critical protection
- **Banking** - financial security
- **Social media** - identity protection
- **Work systems** - business protection
:::

---

## Password Best Practices {background-image="/assets/background1.png" background-size="cover"}

::: incremental
- **Minimum 12 characters**
- **Mix of upper, lower, numbers, symbols**
- **Never reuse across accounts**
- **Consider passkeys when available**
:::

---

## Operating System Security {.center background-image="/assets/slide1.png" background-size="cover"}

> "Keep your systems updated"

---

## Enable Automatic Updates {background-image="/assets/background1.png" background-size="cover"}

::: incremental
- Operating system patches
- Security updates get priority
- Configure automatic restarts
- Don't delay critical updates
:::

---

## Use Supported Systems {background-image="/assets/slide1.png" background-size="cover"}

::: incremental
- Avoid end-of-life operating systems
- Plan regular OS upgrades
- Verify vendor security support
- Legacy systems = security risk
:::

---

## Built-in Security Features {background-image="/assets/background1.png" background-size="cover"}

::: incremental
- **Windows Defender** - enable it
- **macOS XProtect** - built-in protection
- **Built-in firewalls** - turn them on
- **Real-time protection** - keep it active
:::

---

## Remote Access Security {.center background-image="/assets/slide1.png" background-size="cover"}

> "Remote access can be exploited by attackers"

---

## Disable RDP Unless Necessary {background-image="/assets/background1.png" background-size="cover"}

::: incremental
- Business operations only
- Alternative solutions preferred
- Regular usage audits
- Most home users don't need it
:::

---

## Secure Remote Access {background-image="/assets/slide1.png" background-size="cover"}

::: incremental
- **VPN connections** mandatory
- **Strong authentication** required
- **Monitor access logs** regularly
- **Use dedicated solutions** when possible
:::

---

## Browser Security {.center background-image="/assets/background1.png" background-size="cover"}

> "Web browsers are common attack vectors"

---

## Keep Browsers Updated {background-image="/assets/slide1.png" background-size="cover"}

::: incremental
- Enable automatic browser updates
- Update extensions regularly
- Install security patches promptly
- Outdated browsers = vulnerable
:::

---

## Manage Active Content {background-image="/assets/background1.png" background-size="cover"}

::: incremental
- Disable JavaScript when not needed
- Manage Java and ActiveX carefully
- Review plugin security regularly
- Less active content = less risk
:::

---

## Browser Extensions {background-image="/assets/slide1.png" background-size="cover"}

::: incremental
- **Regular review and removal**
- **Trust only reputable sources**
- **Minimal permissions principle**
- **Use ad blockers for protection**
:::

---

## Email Security {.center background-image="/assets/background1.png" background-size="cover"}

> "Email remains a primary attack vector"

---

## Suspicious Attachments {background-image="/assets/slide1.png" background-size="cover"}

::: incremental
- **Never open from unknown senders**
- **Verify unexpected attachments**
- **Use alternative communication channels**
- **When in doubt, don't open it**
:::

---

## Link Verification {background-image="/assets/background1.png" background-size="cover"}

::: incremental
- **Hover to preview URLs**
- **Check for suspicious domains**
- **Avoid shortened links**
- **Look for typos in URLs**
:::

---

## Social Engineering Awareness {background-image="/assets/slide1.png" background-size="cover"}

::: incremental
- Urgent requests for money/credentials
- Impersonation attempts
- Pressure tactics recognition
- Trust your instincts
:::

---

## Wi-Fi Security {.center background-image="/assets/background1.png" background-size="cover"}

> "Secure your wireless connections"

---

## Strong Encryption {background-image="/assets/slide1.png" background-size="cover"}

::: incremental
- **WPA3 preferred** (WPA2 minimum)
- **Strong wireless passwords**
- **Regular password changes**
- **Avoid WEP encryption**
:::

---

## Router Security {background-image="/assets/background1.png" background-size="cover"}

::: incremental
- **Change default credentials**
- **Update firmware regularly**
- **Disable WPS functionality**
- **Use generic network names**
:::

---

## Data Backup Strategy {.center background-image="/assets/slide1.png" background-size="cover"}

> "The 3-2-1 Backup Rule"

---

## The 3-2-1 Rule Explained {background-image="/assets/background1.png" background-size="cover"}

::: incremental
- **3 copies** of important data
- **2 different media types**
- **1 copy stored offsite**
:::

---

## Backup Best Practices {background-image="/assets/slide1.png" background-size="cover"}

::: incremental
- **Store backups offline** (air-gapped)
- **Test restoration procedures** regularly
- **Encrypt backup data**
- **Automate the process**
:::

